Add an External Service Action

Deliver personalized customer experiences without writing a single line of code.

To build and manage Einstein Bots:

Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots

Before you begin, make sure that the external service you want to integrate with your dialog is registered in your Salesforce org. From the Dialog Component Library, drag the External Service Action step onto the canvas.
In the Step Properties panel, select the name of the external service associated with your desired action, and then select the action.
Specify input and output variables.

Supported variables:

Text
Number
Boolean
Object
Date
DateTime
Currency
Id
A single-level list

Save the dialog.

When an external service action is used in a bot dialog, you can’t edit the settings for the associated service or delete the service from your Salesforce org. To edit or delete an external service, confirm that it’s not included in any bot dialogs.

What’s a Variable?
